{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Kurki et al. (2016) and Rietdijk et al. (2018) tapped into SR to explore how instructors use various teaching strategies and their underlying beliefs, particularly concerning non-cognitive dimensions such as social and emotional factors.",
    "Aside from its application as an educational research method, SR can also serve as an effective teaching and learning strategy.",
    "Instructors can use SR to assess what learners remember or may have overlooked to determine learning reinforcement strategies.",
    "SR enables learners to examine and articulate their thoughts through memory retrieval and thus elevating their thinking to a new level of expression.",
    "Therefore, SR can enhance learning rather than solely serving as a research approach (Smagorinsky, 1998; Egi, 2008)."
  ]
}